	     Juba - Fifty people were killed in raids by a tribal militia in eastern South Sudan, a local official said on Wednesday, the latest in a series of attacks between rival communities. Dut Achuek, a state minister, said eight people died in an attack on Monday in Jonglei state, while a follow-up raid on Tuesday left "23 women killed and... 19 men killed." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  